            <title>[LU-14437] Use NSEC_PER_USEC when converting between NSEC and USEC values</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14437</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Andreas noted that (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14080&quot; title=&quot;gnilnd updates for 5.3+ kernel changes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14080&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14080&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; gnilnd: updates for SUSE 15 SP2&quot;) introduced a defect where an incorrect constant was used to convert from usec to msec.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In general the constant: NSEC_PER_USEC should be used.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
